# Fried Rice with Prawns and Bacon

## Ingredients
- @eggs{2}
- @bacon{4 slices}
- @peanut oil{3 tablespoons}
- @garlic{2 cloves (minced)}
- @ginger{1 tablespoon (grated)}
- @onion{1/2 cup (chopped)}
- @prawns{1 cup}
- @rice{2 cups (cooked)}
- @oyster sauce{2 tablespoons}
- @soy sauce{2 tablespoons}
- @sesame oil{2 teaspoons}
- @scallions{1/4 cup (thinly sliced)}

## Instructions
1. `mix @oyster sauce + @soy sauce{1 tablespoon} + @sesame oil{1 teaspoon}`
2. `heat @peanut oil{2 tablespoons} in #wok or #skillet on medium`
3. `add @eggs -> scramble -> remove to plate`
4. `increase heat to high -> add @bacon -> cook until golden -> remove to plate with egg`
5. `drain excess fat from @bacon`
6. `add @peanut oil{1 tablespoon} + @garlic + @ginger -> return #wok to stove on high`
7. `stir-fry until @garlic sizzles -> add @onion -> stir-fry for 2 minutes`
8. `add @prawns -> cook until pink`
9. `add @rice + @oyster sauce mixture + @soy sauce{1 tablespoon} + @sesame oil{1 teaspoon} -> stir-fry`
10. `top with @scallions -> serve`
```

